WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:52.970
Straw Hat Luffy...

3
00:01:52.970 --> 00:01:54.930
What a fitting end to your story...

4
00:01:54.970 --> 00:01:57.390
Croc-ish

5
00:01:58.010 --> 00:02:01.850
In about six minutes, this yard
will explode along with the square.

6
00:02:01.850 --> 00:02:04.400
Apologies, but I'm on a tight schedule.

7
00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:07.360
You just sit back
and celebrate the coronation...

8
00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:10.360
of the Kingdom of Sand's new ruler.

9
00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:14.200
Well, then...

10
00:02:17.490 --> 00:02:19.490
I should also be on my way.

11
00:02:19.490 --> 00:02:21.950
He said the mortuary temple
is west of here...

12
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:33.220
You missed...

13
00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:46.520
That was close!
I thought I was a goner!

14
00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:53.360
That jerk... He's gone now...

15
00:02:55.030 --> 00:02:57.320
I saw him flying that way!

16
00:02:57.740 --> 00:02:59.330
I won't let him get away!

17
00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:00.830
That damn croc!

18
00:03:00.830 --> 00:03:05.080
Mortuary Temple
(Royal Mausoleum)
West of the Palace

19
00:03:11.630 --> 00:03:14.220
So this is the royal mausoleum...

20
00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:17.050
the final resting place
for generations of kings.

21
00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:21.180
Where's the poneglyph?

22
00:03:33.740 --> 00:03:34.740
A hidden passage!

23
00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:39.660
The poneglyph lies deep underground.

24
00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:44.700
Most people aren't even aware
of the poneglyphs' existence.

25
00:03:44.700 --> 00:03:46.710
The criminal underworld is vast.

26
00:03:46.710 --> 00:03:51.920
Even the kings under 
the World Government don't know everything.

27
00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:54.210
Don't beat yourself up.

28
00:03:55.300 --> 00:04:00.510
You probably didn't know there was
someone out there who could read them.

29
00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:02.640
You can read poneglyphs?

30
00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:03.770
Yes...

31
00:04:03.770 --> 00:04:07.270
That's why Crocodile and I teamed up.

32
00:04:07.270 --> 00:04:09.730
Because of that,
I'm indispensable to him.

33
00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:15.820
It's likely that the poneglyph in this country
has the location of Pluton inscribed on it.

34
00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:16.650
Am I right?

35
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:18.530
I have no idea.

36
00:04:18.530 --> 00:04:22.740
Alabasta's royal family has been tasked
with protecting it for generations.

37
00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:25.120
That's all it is to us.

38
00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:26.620
Protecting it?

39
00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:27.580
Don't make me laugh!

40
00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:36.260
Quite impressive...

41
00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:38.840
It rests beyond the doors at the end.

42
00:04:47.350 --> 00:04:48.940
Indeed...

43
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:00.280
You vermin...

44
00:05:01.360 --> 00:05:02.620
What's wrong with you?!

45
00:05:03.030 --> 00:05:06.200
What?! I'm trying to put
myself in Crocodile's shoes!

46
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:08.580
Like, "Where would I
shoot a cannon from?!"

47
00:05:08.580 --> 00:05:11.040
Well, stop! We've got
five minutes to find it!

48
00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:14.920
Five minutes! A million lives
will be lost in five more minutes!

49
00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:18.050
We've gotta hurry...! We've gotta
hurry up and find the cannoneer!

50
00:05:18.050 --> 00:05:20.510
Chopper! Can't you just
sniff this guy out?!

51
00:05:20.510 --> 00:05:23.720
I'm sorry, but all I can smell
right now is gunpowder!

52
00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:25.390
Then... listen!

53
00:05:25.390 --> 00:05:28.980
Can you sniff out "a guy who's
aiming a cannon at the square"?

54
00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:30.270
How does that smell?!

55
00:05:30.270 --> 00:05:32.190
How should I know?! Just try!

56
00:05:32.190 --> 00:05:33.350
What?!

57
00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:38.730
It can level a five-kilometer area...

58
00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:42.780
Wait! Then it's gotta be pretty big...

59
00:05:42.780 --> 00:05:46.280
And if it's being fired from
a cannon, it can't go very far...

60
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:49.250
Then it's closer to
the square after all?!

61
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.120
I don't have time to go around!

62
00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:53.960
I'm making a shortcut!

63
00:05:55.250 --> 00:05:56.460
Find anything, Pell?!

64
00:05:56.460 --> 00:06:01.090
I checked every rooftop near the square,
but there were no signs of a cannon!

65
00:06:01.510 --> 00:06:04.300
Then... maybe it's inside
one of these buildings...!

66
00:06:04.300 --> 00:06:05.720
I'll search every last one!

67
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:06.760
All right!

68
00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:21.610
What's it going to take
for you to just stay down?!

69
00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:34.960
Crocodile...

70
00:06:36.460 --> 00:06:39.210
Looks like you were
no match for her...

71
00:06:39.210 --> 00:06:42.630
I'm surprised the Marines
followed me all the way here.

72
00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:45.510
Where's your boss?

73
00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:47.890
Did that smoke bastard run away?

74
00:06:48.470 --> 00:06:51.060
Losers shouldn't preach about justice.

75
00:06:51.060 --> 00:06:53.680
This sea is for the mighty.

76
00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:57.810
If you want to prattle on about justice,
do it from the safety of your base.

77
00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:09.700
Crocodile!

78
00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:22.340
Straw Hat!

79
00:07:23.130 --> 00:07:25.300
Where did... that damn croc go?!

80
00:07:27.970 --> 00:07:29.010
Tell me!

81
00:07:29.010 --> 00:07:30.180
Where's that croc?!

82
00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:48.450
He's headed toward
the mortuary temple.

83
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:50.450
That way?! Thanks!

84
00:08:04.210 --> 00:08:06.090
What justice...?

85
00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:16.020
To hell with Marine Headquarters...!

86
00:08:25.230 --> 00:08:26.490
Oh?

87
00:08:26.490 --> 00:08:28.200
I'm having trouble moving...

88
00:08:30.030 --> 00:08:32.950
That's weird... I ate plenty of meat...

89
00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:35.660
What's wrong?
It's just some scratches...

90
00:08:36.790 --> 00:08:39.460
Maybe... I'm a little tired...

91
00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:45.960
Did it tell you what
you wanted to know?

92
00:08:53.430 --> 00:08:55.390
Ah, there we are...

93
00:08:55.390 --> 00:08:57.600
A hidden staircase.

94
00:09:02.690 --> 00:09:05.190
Four... Four more minutes...!

95
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:29.260
Aren't there more?

96
00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:31.800
This country isn't hiding any others?

97
00:09:31.800 --> 00:09:33.800
Are you not satisfied?

98
00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:36.010
I did as you asked.

99
00:09:37.770 --> 00:09:38.930
That you did...

100
00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.440
Now this is what you call
a national secret...

101
00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:48.860
Try as you might, you'd never find it
without knowledge of its location.

102
00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:52.740
So, Nico Robin...
this is the poneglyph?

103
00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:55.570
That didn't take long.

104
00:09:56.370 --> 00:09:58.870
It's strange, huh...?

105
00:09:58.870 --> 00:10:00.870
Were you able to decipher it?

106
00:10:00.870 --> 00:10:02.120
Yes.

107
00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:05.290
Good. Now, read
the so-called poneglyph...

108
00:10:09.380 --> 00:10:14.840
In the empyreal year 239...
Kahire conquered Alabasta.

109
00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:18.970
In the year 260, Tamer
of the Bytine dynasty ruled.

110
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:23.810
In 306, the Taf Cathedral
was completed in Erumalu.

111
00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:27.270
In 325, the hero Mamudine of Oltair–

112
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:28.690
Hey, quit screwing around!

113
00:10:28.690 --> 00:10:31.440
You think that's what
we've been looking for?!

114
00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:34.030
Who cares about
this country's history?!

115
00:10:34.030 --> 00:10:38.160
Tell me where I can find the world's
most destructive military power!

116
00:10:38.530 --> 00:10:40.410
Where is Pluton?!

117
00:10:41.620 --> 00:10:43.080
It doesn't say.

118
00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:44.250
Huh?!

119
00:10:44.250 --> 00:10:46.750
The only thing recorded 
here is history.

120
00:10:46.750 --> 00:10:47.840
What?!

121
00:10:47.840 --> 00:10:49.090
Pluton...

122
00:10:49.090 --> 00:10:52.550
That name isn't mentioned here once.

123
00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:56.050
Well...

124
00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:57.300
I see...

125
00:10:57.300 --> 00:10:58.970
What a pity.

126
00:10:59.850 --> 00:11:02.930
You've been an exceptional partner, but...

127
00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:05.390
you've outlived your usefulness.

128
00:11:05.900 --> 00:11:06.600
What...?!

129
00:11:08.150 --> 00:11:12.740
The terms of our agreement from
four years ago have just been met.

130
00:11:12.740 --> 00:11:15.650
Back then, you came
to me with a promise...

131
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:18.030
that if I could get you
to the poneglyph,

132
00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:21.040
you'd tell me all I need
to know about the weapon.

133
00:11:21.620 --> 00:11:25.000
In terms of both
intellect and leadership,

134
00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:27.830
your work these past
four years has been superb.

135
00:11:28.670 --> 00:11:30.920
At least in those regards...

136
00:11:30.920 --> 00:11:33.800
you managed to be useful to me.

137
00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:35.300
But...

138
00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:38.010
you couldn't keep up
your end of the bargain!

139
00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:44.600
This poneglyph holds no
information concerning Pluton!

140
00:11:45.850 --> 00:11:47.770
Or...

141
00:11:47.770 --> 00:11:52.820
maybe you never intended to tell me,
regardless of what you found?

142
00:11:57.660 --> 00:11:58.990
Even so...

143
00:11:58.990 --> 00:12:01.780
I harbor no grudge against you.

144
00:12:01.780 --> 00:12:04.620
Do you know why, Nico Robin?

145
00:12:05.250 --> 00:12:07.750
Ridiculous... We've been
partners for four years!

146
00:12:07.750 --> 00:12:10.920
Of course you'd pull
something like this!

147
00:12:11.840 --> 00:12:13.210
Water?!

148
00:12:13.210 --> 00:12:15.380
I can stab you once
you're wet, right?!

149
00:12:17.970 --> 00:12:19.800
He dodged it! Where'd he–

150
00:12:24.390 --> 00:12:27.850
I forgive you for everything,
Nico Robin...

151
00:12:34.780 --> 00:12:37.030
After all...

152
00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:40.240
from the very beginning...

153
00:12:40.240 --> 00:12:42.990
I never trusted anyone.

154
00:12:47.750 --> 00:12:52.250
Cobra's reaction confirmed
Pluton's existence to me.

155
00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:55.750
I'll find it on my own.
I no longer need the poneglyph.

156
00:12:55.750 --> 00:12:58.880
Once this country is mine,
it's only a matter of time.

157
00:13:01.260 --> 00:13:04.350
What's happening? It's too soon
for the attack on the square!

158
00:13:05.600 --> 00:13:07.680
You... What did you do?

159
00:13:07.680 --> 00:13:12.100
Oh, nothing major. This tomb
is built in such a way

160
00:13:12.100 --> 00:13:16.070
that removing one small column
destabilizes the structure,

161
00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:18.570
destroying the entire temple.

162
00:13:18.570 --> 00:13:23.450
You two... will perish here with me.

163
00:13:23.450 --> 00:13:27.830
As the twelfth king
of the Nefertari dynasty,

164
00:13:27.830 --> 00:13:31.540
I cannot allow someone like you
to seize the Kingdom of Sand.

165
00:13:33.790 --> 00:13:37.670
Outstanding... An example
for kings everywhere!

166
00:13:37.670 --> 00:13:42.760
You're willing to die down here
with me to protect your country?

167
00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:45.220
Unfortunately... you can't kill me.

168
00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:50.180
I'll simply change the bedrock
to sand and make my escape.

169
00:13:51.350 --> 00:13:53.650
Your death will be for naught, Cobra.

170
00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:57.150
There's less than
three minutes remaining.

171
00:13:57.150 --> 00:13:59.780
When the temple collapses
and the square blows up,

172
00:13:59.780 --> 00:14:03.610
all my obstacles
will vanish in an instant!

173
00:14:04.110 --> 00:14:06.740
In that moment, this land...

174
00:14:06.740 --> 00:14:09.040
will become my country!

175
00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:32.270
Where is it?

176
00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:34.020
Only three more minutes...

177
00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:37.150
A cannon with
a five-kilometer blast area…

178
00:14:37.150 --> 00:14:40.610
There can't be many places
where such a thing would fit...

179
00:14:40.610 --> 00:14:44.110
We're searching so hard,
so why can't we find it...?!

180
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:47.240
An open space where
a big cannon can fit...

181
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:49.120
A stray bullet!

182
00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:52.450
An open space...

183
00:14:54.120 --> 00:14:57.920
Hey, no fair, Koza! You were
hiding in a place like this?!

184
00:14:57.920 --> 00:15:00.000
Leader! No fair!

185
00:15:00.380 --> 00:15:01.670
That's it...!

186
00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:03.260
That place can...

187
00:15:03.260 --> 00:15:05.630
Watch where you're aiming, jerk!

188
00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:06.340
Smoke Star!

189
00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:09.510
It's unassuming while
providing plenty of space.

190
00:15:10.180 --> 00:15:11.850
I'm not with the Rebel Army!

191
00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:13.100
Usopp Hammer!

192
00:15:13.100 --> 00:15:15.480
Usopp's Rubber Band of Doom!

193
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:16.900
Learn your lesson, bastard?

194
00:15:16.900 --> 00:15:19.650
Man, who do they think I am...?!

195
00:15:19.650 --> 00:15:21.940
Don't be shocked by this!
Actually, be shocked!

196
00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:24.900
I am the famous Captain–

197
00:15:24.900 --> 00:15:28.320
What? O-Oh, it's you, Vivi.
Did you find the cannoneer?

198
00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:30.200
I figured it out! I know where it is!

199
00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:31.540
What?! Really?!

200
00:15:31.540 --> 00:15:34.040
Okay, then! I'll signal them!

201
00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:36.830
This should get their attention!
You're sure, right?!

202
00:15:37.960 --> 00:15:39.130
Lethal...

203
00:15:39.670 --> 00:15:41.590
Red Serpent Star!

204
00:16:17.540 --> 00:16:19.920
Man, I slept like a baby.

205
00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:22.000
Huh...? Oh, that's right.

206
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.630
I couldn't move all of a sudden...

207
00:16:24.630 --> 00:16:28.430
so I figured a nap wouldn't hurt.

208
00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:31.890
And now I feel better, so...

209
00:16:31.890 --> 00:16:32.640
Oh, yeah!

210
00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:36.600
I'm gonna beat
the crap outta that croc!

211
00:16:46.190 --> 00:16:47.740
That hole...

212
00:16:51.570 --> 00:16:53.160
looks croc-ish...!

213
00:16:54.990 --> 00:16:57.080
What's with this place?

214
00:16:58.410 --> 00:17:00.370
It's falling apart!

215
00:17:11.430 --> 00:17:13.300
There's no mistake!

216
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:17.060
The cannoneer has to be there!
I finally figured it out!

217
00:17:17.060 --> 00:17:19.890
Are you sure it's there, Vivi?!

218
00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:23.230
If this storm is part of his plan...

219
00:17:24.150 --> 00:17:27.650
it should be a place where
they can still hit the target...

220
00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:34.030
It also has to be large enough
to house the cannon

221
00:17:34.030 --> 00:17:36.080
while being hidden from the sky!

222
00:17:36.740 --> 00:17:39.250
Look! This place is pretty big, right?!

223
00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:42.540
Why don't we make it
our secret base?

224
00:17:42.540 --> 00:17:43.670
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

225
00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:46.550
It's the only place I can think of!

226
00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:50.010
Then give me a second! Everyone's
on their way, so I'll leave a message...

227
00:17:50.420 --> 00:17:52.720
I'm gonna go on ahead, Usopp!

228
00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:55.050
What?! W-Wait, Vivi! W-Wait!

229
00:17:55.050 --> 00:17:56.140
Hurry!

230
00:17:55.430 --> 00:17:56.140
Oh, okay.

231
00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:59.060
Alright, we found her!

232
00:17:59.060 --> 00:18:01.060
It's the princess!

233
00:18:02.270 --> 00:18:05.190
That signal led us right to her!

234
00:18:05.940 --> 00:18:07.940
More Baroque Works operatives...?!

235
00:18:09.650 --> 00:18:11.400
I led the bad guys right to us!

236
00:18:13.070 --> 00:18:15.240
That's Usopp's signal.

237
00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:18.290
But why is the palace so far away?!

238
00:18:19.870 --> 00:18:21.540
Good, it's close!

239
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.330
I wonder if they found the cannoneer.

240
00:18:24.330 --> 00:18:26.590
They must have! Hurry!

241
00:18:28.090 --> 00:18:29.760
Usopp...

242
00:18:29.760 --> 00:18:32.470
Noise...!

243
00:18:38.180 --> 00:18:40.970
So this is... This is my...

244
00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:42.560
Now! Let's go, Vivi!

245
00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:44.060
Okay!

246
00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:46.190
Th-They ran away!

247
00:18:46.610 --> 00:18:48.320
Stop right there!

248
00:19:08.790 --> 00:19:10.050
You...!

249
00:19:10.670 --> 00:19:13.010
I've got you now, you damn croc!

250
00:19:14.630 --> 00:19:16.510
How are you still alive?!

251
00:19:16.510 --> 00:19:21.010
I kill you and I kill you, so why
do you continue to stand against me?!

252
00:19:21.350 --> 00:19:23.480
Well?! Straw Hat!

253
00:19:23.480 --> 00:19:27.230
Why is he here? So he was still alive?

254
00:19:27.230 --> 00:19:29.440
Just who is this young man...?

255
00:19:35.950 --> 00:19:37.410
Straw Hat...

256
00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:43.250
How many times
do I have to kill you?!

257
00:19:43.580 --> 00:19:46.370
You still haven't given back...

258
00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:48.000
what you took!

259
00:19:49.040 --> 00:19:50.460
What I took?!

260
00:19:50.960 --> 00:19:52.250
Do you mean money?

261
00:19:52.710 --> 00:19:53.920
Fame?

262
00:19:54.590 --> 00:19:56.050
Trust?

263
00:19:56.720 --> 00:19:58.140
Lives?

264
00:19:58.470 --> 00:19:59.850
Rain?!

265
00:20:03.970 --> 00:20:05.980
What exactly do you
want me to return?!

266
00:20:05.980 --> 00:20:08.690
I've lost track of all
the things I've taken!

267
00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:10.610
This country!

268
00:20:11.520 --> 00:20:12.900
This country?

269
00:20:12.900 --> 00:20:15.400
You say the damnedest things.

270
00:20:15.400 --> 00:20:21.910
This country is about to be mine...
I shall become its new king!

271
00:20:23.200 --> 00:20:27.870
When we got here,
it was already long gone.

272
00:20:28.370 --> 00:20:30.000
Her country...!

273
00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:36.590
I have to reason
with the Rebel Army...

274
00:20:36.590 --> 00:20:39.470
because I want this bloodshed
to finally come to an end!

275
00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:47.890
Not long ago, this city
was a verdant paradise.

276
00:20:50.150 --> 00:20:52.020
Please, Vivi!

277
00:20:52.610 --> 00:20:56.360
You have to stop those fools!

278
00:20:56.440 --> 00:20:59.360
If this is really her country...

279
00:21:01.070 --> 00:21:02.570
What's wrong...

280
00:21:02.570 --> 00:21:05.200
with not wanting people to die?!

281
00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:09.710
Just one look at this kingdom
and even I can tell...

282
00:21:11.170 --> 00:21:13.080
what needs to be done!

283
00:21:15.710 --> 00:21:19.760
Do you think it's enough
to risk your life alone?!

284
00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:21.430
I've got–

285
00:21:23.760 --> 00:21:27.720
I-I've got nothing else to give...

286
00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:33.730
Why don't you try risking
all of our lives together?!

287
00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.190
Aren't we friends?!

288
00:21:41.660 --> 00:21:44.780
If this really is her country...

289
00:21:44.780 --> 00:21:46.030
she should be...

290
00:21:46.030 --> 00:21:47.950
smiling more!

291
00:21:50.660 --> 00:21:55.380
Big talk, but without any water,
you can't even land a single–

292
00:22:05.930 --> 00:22:07.430
It can't be...

293
00:22:07.430 --> 00:22:10.640
He kicked me without
using any water...

294
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:16.980
If only you hadn't come
to this country...

295
00:22:16.980 --> 00:22:19.940
Alabasta would've remained peaceful!

296
00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:23.150
Isn't it just heartrending?

297
00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:27.580
Love for this country is what
will lead to its destruction.

298
00:22:35.710 --> 00:22:37.090
Crocodile!

299
00:22:37.090 --> 00:22:37.630
Wai–

300
00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:54.270
Could it be... you're using...

301
00:22:57.610 --> 00:22:58.690
your own blood...?

302
00:23:00.190 --> 00:23:02.860
Blood can harden sand too, right?

303
00:23:13.330 --> 00:23:16.250
From Rainbase... to the palace...

304
00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:19.170
all the way to the mortuary temple...

305
00:23:20.750 --> 00:23:24.670
Since you climbed your way
out of hell twice to challenge me,

306
00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:27.220
I'll reward your persistence...

307
00:23:27.550 --> 00:23:28.760
You bastard...!

308
00:23:32.850 --> 00:23:35.190
...like a pirate!

309
00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:40.520
It seems you'll stop
at nothing to take me down.

310
00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:45.490
I have to admit, you've become
a real thorn in my side.

311
00:23:46.400 --> 00:23:47.530
It came off!

312
00:23:47.530 --> 00:23:48.530
What the...?

313
00:23:49.870 --> 00:23:51.280
It's a venomous hook.

314
00:23:51.660 --> 00:23:52.620
That right?

315
00:23:53.080 --> 00:23:57.580
If you're the real deal,
you should know...

316
00:23:58.120 --> 00:24:02.130
that a duel between pirates
is a fight to the death.

317
00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:05.420
There's no such thing
as "fighting dirty."

318
00:24:13.810 --> 00:24:18.520
When the square explodes,
this tomb will collapse as well.

319
00:24:18.520 --> 00:24:20.690
This is the last time...

320
00:24:20.690 --> 00:24:22.820
This ends right here, right now!

321
00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:29.320
The smoke was in
that direction, right?

322
00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:32.370
No, was it this way?

323
00:24:34.290 --> 00:24:36.120
What?! Marines?!

324
00:24:36.120 --> 00:24:38.080
Look! It's Roronoa Zoro!

325
00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:41.500
Dammit! I didn't realize the Marines
were running around here, too...!

326
00:24:41.500 --> 00:24:43.590
There's no time to spare...

327
00:24:43.590 --> 00:24:45.010
Guess I've gotta fight!

328
00:24:45.010 --> 00:24:47.050
I'll settle this in three seconds!

329
00:24:47.050 --> 00:24:49.680
You...! Why are you here?!

330
00:24:49.680 --> 00:24:51.010
What are you doing?!

331
00:24:51.430 --> 00:24:53.470
Hey, that's my line!

332
00:24:53.470 --> 00:24:54.600
Roronoa Zoro!

333
00:24:54.970 --> 00:24:58.600
Back the way you came, north from
the last corner is the square!

334
00:24:59.100 --> 00:25:01.100
Go back and turn right! Not this way!

335
00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:02.360
Are you stupid?!

336
00:25:02.360 --> 00:25:03.610
Stupid?!

337
00:25:03.610 --> 00:25:04.400
Hurry up!

338
00:25:04.400 --> 00:25:05.070
Go!

339
00:25:05.070 --> 00:25:06.740
Wh-What?!

340
00:25:06.740 --> 00:25:08.030
What's going on?!

341
00:25:11.990 --> 00:25:14.370
Wait! Hold it!

342
00:25:30.930 --> 00:25:32.680
Th-Tha... Thank...

343
00:25:33.510 --> 00:25:35.680
We'll cover you!

344
00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:38.640
Please, stop the bombing
of the square! Now, hurry!

345
00:25:39.140 --> 00:25:41.270
Thank you! Hurry, Usopp!

346
00:25:41.270 --> 00:25:42.600
Uh... Right!

347
00:25:56.120 --> 00:25:58.410
Hurry! Hurry!

348
00:25:58.790 --> 00:26:00.040
We lost a lot of time!

349
00:26:00.040 --> 00:26:03.880
I don't know why the Marines
helped us, but if they hadn't,

350
00:26:03.880 --> 00:26:06.090
it would've been a lot worse!

351
00:26:16.180 --> 00:26:17.260
Focus, dummy!

352
00:26:18.260 --> 00:26:21.940
If we don't stop this attack,
way more people will die!

353
00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:23.390
Right!

354
00:26:23.390 --> 00:26:27.360
Prayers aren't what'll stop this attack!

355
00:26:30.820 --> 00:26:34.240
We have two minutes! It's do or die!

356
00:26:35.030 --> 00:26:36.740
We still have a minute and a half!

357
00:26:36.740 --> 00:26:37.160
Yes...!

358
00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:38.030
You've got us!

359
00:26:38.030 --> 00:26:38.700
Yes!

360
00:26:43.790 --> 00:26:44.670
There they are!

361
00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:46.460
Vivi! Usopp!

362
00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:49.420
Nami! Tony!

363
00:26:49.800 --> 00:26:50.920
What's going on?!

364
00:26:50.920 --> 00:26:52.670
The Marines helped us!

365
00:26:52.670 --> 00:26:54.380
Did you find the cannoneer?!

366
00:26:55.010 --> 00:26:57.600
We don't have confirmation,
but I'm positive!

367
00:26:58.390 --> 00:27:01.060
I looked at it so many times
but never considered it!

368
00:27:01.520 --> 00:27:04.730
The cannoneer is up there,
no doubt about it!

369
00:27:07.520 --> 00:27:08.610
What?!

370
00:27:10.110 --> 00:27:11.320
The clock tower...

371
00:27:11.320 --> 00:27:12.360
I see!

372
00:27:12.360 --> 00:27:14.780
They'd have a great
shot from up there!

373
00:27:15.200 --> 00:27:18.240
If only Pell was here,
we could put a stop to this...!

374
00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:20.290
Pell...!

375
00:27:29.750 --> 00:27:31.550
We're running out of time!

376
00:27:32.210 --> 00:27:36.380
If I'm not mistaken, the smoke
was rising from here, but...

377
00:27:37.550 --> 00:27:39.890
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

378
00:27:39.890 --> 00:27:41.060
Hey, listen.

379
00:27:41.060 --> 00:27:45.310
I just nailed one hell of a bird
with my Ribbit-Ribbit Gun!

380
00:27:50.610 --> 00:27:52.230
I was careless...!

381
00:28:39.610 --> 00:28:41.990
Gum-Gum Pisto–

382
00:29:43.760 --> 00:29:46.510
Who in the world is he...?

383
00:29:47.100 --> 00:29:53.060
Crocodile crushed our mightiest
warriors like mere insects, and yet...

384
00:30:00.650 --> 00:30:04.530
I skewered you, buried you alive,
and even mummified you...

385
00:30:06.620 --> 00:30:11.160
but even you, who stood
back up after all that...

386
00:30:11.160 --> 00:30:13.000
won't be able to survive this.

387
00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:17.000
Our game is at an end. That venom
will soon spread throughout your body.

388
00:30:17.880 --> 00:30:21.260
You just don't get it!

389
00:30:23.010 --> 00:30:24.470
I wonder what happened...

390
00:30:26.180 --> 00:30:28.720
I don't see Pell anywhere...

391
00:30:29.310 --> 00:30:30.640
Hey, Vivi.

392
00:30:30.640 --> 00:30:34.560
We can't get all the way up there
in a minute! Not by ourselves!

393
00:30:34.560 --> 00:30:36.730
Pell! Where are you?! Hurry!

394
00:30:37.190 --> 00:30:39.480
At this point, we have to try!

395
00:30:39.900 --> 00:30:41.780
We'll take the stairs! Here's the entra–

396
00:30:41.780 --> 00:30:43.610
Hey!

397
00:30:43.610 --> 00:30:44.360
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

398
00:30:44.360 --> 00:30:47.330
Nami, my sweet! Vivi, my love!

399
00:30:47.330 --> 00:30:49.830
What are you doing up there?!

400
00:30:49.830 --> 00:30:51.000
What do you mean?!

401
00:30:51.000 --> 00:30:54.290
You left a message under
the smoke, didn't you?!

402
00:30:54.670 --> 00:30:58.290
It said "clock tower,"
so I came up here.

403
00:30:59.300 --> 00:31:00.210
What should I do?

404
00:31:00.880 --> 00:31:02.720
Where's the cannoneer?

405
00:31:02.720 --> 00:31:04.880
He's at the top! The top!

406
00:31:04.880 --> 00:31:06.640
Go up there and kick some ass!

407
00:31:06.640 --> 00:31:07.180
Huh?

408
00:31:07.550 --> 00:31:08.810
Huh? Wha...?!

409
00:31:08.810 --> 00:31:11.310
Hey, I looked all over for you guys!

410
00:31:11.310 --> 00:31:13.430
Zoro! You too?!

411
00:31:13.430 --> 00:31:15.020
What're you doing there?

412
00:31:15.020 --> 00:31:17.310
That's my line, moron!

413
00:31:17.310 --> 00:31:21.320
Well, the Marines kept
telling me to go north,

414
00:31:21.320 --> 00:31:22.990
so I came up here!

415
00:31:22.990 --> 00:31:25.280
"North" and "up" are totally
different, dumbass!

416
00:31:25.280 --> 00:31:27.240
Well in any case, nice work!

417
00:31:27.240 --> 00:31:30.830
Keep heading up
and trash that clock tower!

418
00:31:30.830 --> 00:31:31.950
They can't!

419
00:31:31.290 --> 00:31:31.950
What?!

420
00:31:32.410 --> 00:31:35.580
The tower is inaccessible
from their current location.

421
00:31:35.580 --> 00:31:41.090
Unless you're flying, the only way in
is a staircase at the back of the first floor.

422
00:31:41.670 --> 00:31:44.300
But Zoro could just smash
through the tower walls...

423
00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:48.550
The cannonball might
explode from the shock!

424
00:31:48.550 --> 00:31:50.760
We'll have to climb the stairs after all!

425
00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:52.010
Wait, Vivi!

426
00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:52.600
What?

427
00:31:53.390 --> 00:31:55.060
I've got an idea!

428
00:32:00.020 --> 00:32:03.230
Ribbit... ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

429
00:32:10.660 --> 00:32:12.540
Hey listen, Mr. 7.

430
00:32:12.540 --> 00:32:16.500
This will be our final mission.

431
00:32:16.500 --> 00:32:19.000
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

432
00:32:18.080 --> 00:32:24.260
Mr. 7

Frontier Agent
Baroque Works
Ms. Father's Day

Frontier Agent
Baroque Works

433
00:32:20.250 --> 00:32:22.170
That's the plan.

434
00:32:24.170 --> 00:32:27.470
According to the plan,
we have thirty seconds left.

435
00:32:30.140 --> 00:32:31.300
Who are they?!

436
00:32:31.300 --> 00:32:34.720
Mr. 7 and Miss Father's Day!
